snippet.textDisplay:
Wow! The exact same thing happened to me with a striped kitten I had. After I unknowingly brought the imposter inside, we left to go out and eat. When we returned, he had torn the shit out of the entire apartment, because apparently he was feral. I didn't know this, so I was obviously quite confused.
The next morning, my real cat came back home and got in a fight with the imposter cat. Got to hand it to the little scrapper, he kicked that impostor right out of the house.
"This is my fuck'n house, my fuck'n food bowl, my fuck'n bed, my fuck'n litter box and my fuck'n humans, now get the fuck out!"
A little add on, an old lady down the road had adopted the feral cat and somehow managed to tame it enough, to be kept as a pet. So everything worked out I guess.
